      "message": "the following two sentences seem contradictory?\n\n1) nothing will show up on the list\n2) \u0027a/\u0027 is selected\n\nbecause a/c/d will show up, which is probably what the user expects?\n\n-----------\n\noverall, to be honest, it is not obvious to me that this problem is worth the complexity this CL is adding: right now the app loads all test results (does not use VARIANTS_WITH_UNEXPECTED_RESULTS) and thus there are a lot of pages to fetch. When Chan adds Stats RPC, we will no longer need to fetch all test results (we can use VARIANTS_WITH_UNEXPECTED_RESULTS), so this problem will become *much* less important, because most of the time all results will fetch the first page-that-we-fetch.\n\nAlso currently app uses pageSize\u003d100. I don\u0027t actually understand this. The app receives 1000 results from the server, but displays only 10% of that and makes the user click \"Load more\" button to see more. If we used same pageSize in loadMore() and in requests, then we\u0027d never be in a state that app has the data, but does not display it.",
